18:18.625 --> 18:19.916
I have a proposition.

18:20.916 --> 18:23.500
-I propose a mutually beneficial--
-I'm not interested.

18:23.583 --> 18:25.166
-Just hear me out, at least.
-No.

18:25.250 --> 18:27.958
-I'll give you half of--
-You hear me! No more credit.

18:28.041 --> 18:30.875
Not to you or anyone else. I've given up!

18:36.125 --> 18:37.083
On what?

18:37.791 --> 18:38.708
Life?

18:58.250 --> 19:00.791
Trust me, I've been close
to throwing in the towel myself.

19:02.083 --> 19:03.250
More than once.

19:04.708 --> 19:06.000
My guess is,

19:06.625 --> 19:08.791
he owed money, which means you owe money.

19:11.625 --> 19:14.000
It's none of my business,
but whatever predicament you're in,

19:14.083 --> 19:16.291
there are better ways out of it
than killing yourself.

19:16.791 --> 19:18.916
By lending money to another addict?

19:23.833 --> 19:25.500
Don't sound so high and mighty.

19:26.875 --> 19:30.166
If you're a broker at a high-end casino,
you make straight commission. You're not.

19:30.708 --> 19:34.041
You make your money from dodgy lines
of credit and illegal side bets.

19:35.083 --> 19:37.333
If you want me to leave, I'll leave.
You can top yourself.

19:37.416 --> 19:39.958
But please don't pretend
you're superior to me.

19:41.208 --> 19:43.833
I may be a gwai lo,
but I still have a soul.

19:44.791 --> 19:46.916
As far as I can see,
it's no more lost than yours.

21:12.250 --> 21:14.333
I should have refused him credit.

21:15.708 --> 21:18.500
I should have told him no, but I didn't.

21:20.125 --> 21:21.291
What was his name?

21:23.166 --> 21:24.750
I've known so many.

21:24.833 --> 21:26.083
You're all the same.

21:27.000 --> 21:28.041
I'm not.

21:28.833 --> 21:32.333
What makes you any different,
apart from being a lord?

21:33.791 --> 21:35.208
My lucky gloves.

21:35.708 --> 21:37.500
Savile Row's finest?

21:40.000 --> 21:40.875
Yes.

21:51.458 --> 21:53.958
It's the Festival of the Hungry Ghost.

21:54.458 --> 21:56.416
In a week, it will be Ghost Day.

21:56.500 --> 21:59.000
That's when people burn offerings
to the dead.

22:17.875 --> 22:19.500
I have to leave here.

22:23.500 --> 22:24.666
So should you.

22:26.208 --> 22:27.041
Where to?

22:29.250 --> 22:30.833
Don't try to follow me.

22:42.500 --> 22:43.875
I was hoping you might

22:45.000 --> 22:46.291
stick around a while.

22:48.583 --> 22:50.041
I'm about to win big.

22:51.500 --> 22:53.833
And when I do,
I won't just pay my debts off.

22:53.916 --> 22:55.166
I'll pay yours too.

22:58.583 --> 22:59.583
Seriously.

23:02.041 --> 23:02.958
Chin up.

23:03.541 --> 23:04.750
It never lasts.

23:06.583 --> 23:08.375
And when my ship comes in, I…

23:10.000 --> 23:10.958
I won't forget you.

23:12.041 --> 23:13.083
That's a promise.

23:13.583 --> 23:15.666
And a lord never goes back on his word.

23:30.958 --> 23:33.208
I have run out of chances.

23:47.708 --> 23:49.041
Keep doing that.

26:04.708 --> 26:06.416
Best foot forward now.

26:08.500 --> 26:10.666
A lord never goes back on his word.

27:16.000 --> 27:16.875
Oh.

27:25.208 --> 27:26.166
Hello.

27:27.833 --> 27:30.000
-Hi.
-Lord Doyle.

27:31.000 --> 27:31.958
I'm sorry?

27:32.041 --> 27:33.750
I… You can call me Freddy.

27:34.458 --> 27:36.333
Oh. Thanks.

27:37.250 --> 27:38.541
First time to Macau?

27:40.541 --> 27:42.666
-I'm sorry?
-I said is it your first trip to Macau?

27:42.750 --> 27:43.583
Yes.

27:44.250 --> 27:46.916
-You?
-No, I come and go.

27:47.000 --> 27:49.458
Oh. That sounds exciting.

27:51.083 --> 27:52.125
I don't mean to be forward,

27:52.208 --> 27:55.041
but I'd be grateful
if you could delete that photo.

27:55.541 --> 27:58.500
-What?
-The one you just took of me in the lift.

27:58.583 --> 28:00.666
Oh… The selfie?

28:00.750 --> 28:02.666
Yes, with me in it.

28:02.750 --> 28:06.333
-Oh, no… Oh, I had no idea you were--
-Well, I… I… I hate to ask.

28:06.416 --> 28:10.083
It's just my privacy means…
it means rather a lot to me.

28:10.583 --> 28:11.583
Why?

28:12.541 --> 28:13.375
Why?

28:13.916 --> 28:15.541
I mean, you're not on the run, are you?

28:16.791 --> 28:19.916
No. No, no, no. It's…
There's no great mystery to it.

28:20.000 --> 28:23.208
It's simply that every genuine high roller
values discretion.

28:23.291 --> 28:25.250
-Oh.
-Yes, discretion is our code.

28:25.333 --> 28:27.000
-Oh, it is, is it?
-It is, actually.

28:27.083 --> 28:28.750
Yeah. Yeah.

28:30.083 --> 28:33.833
Because, actually, you look…
I mean, if I were to say,

28:35.625 --> 28:38.958
like a bit of a show-off
for someone on the lam.

28:42.791 --> 28:44.625
-You didn't tell me your name.
-Betty.

28:44.708 --> 28:46.541
-Betty who?
-Grayson.

28:59.666 --> 29:01.208
Right, then, Betty Grayson.

29:01.291 --> 29:03.000
Who are you? What do you want?

29:03.083 --> 29:04.791
